      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Value other)
        The method for the comparable interface. This is only implemented by numeric types, and allows collections of them to be sorted. By default, the method compares the string form of the values, which gives an arbitrary, but fixed order for such values.

      • convertTo

        public Value convertTo(PType to,
                       Context ctxt)
                throws AnalysisException
        Performing a dynamic type conversion. This method is usually specialized by subclasses that know how to convert themselves to other types. If they fail, they delegate the conversion up to this superclass method which deals with the special cases: unions, type parameters, optional types, bracketed types and named types. If all these also fail, the method throws a runtime dynamic type check exception - though that may be caught, for example by the union processing, as it iterates through the types in the union given, trying to convert the value.
        Parameters:
        to - The target type.
        ctxt - The context in which to make the conversion.
        Returns:
        This value converted to the target type.
        Throws:
        AnalysisException

      • set

        public void set(ILexLocation location,
                Value newval,
                Context ctxt)
         throws ValueException,
                AnalysisException
        Change the object's value. Normally, values are immutable, but subclasses of UpdatableValue implement this set method to replace the object referenced with another. ReferenceValues like UpdatableValue delegate all the other Value method to the contained object.
        Parameters:
        location - Unused.
        newval - The new value to set
        ctxt - The context used
        Throws:
        ValueException
        AnalysisException

      • deref

        public Value deref()
        Find the most primitive underlying value contained. This is typically used to check whether a value is "really" (say) a MapValue once the ReferenceValue (Updatablevalue) wrappers have been removed. Note that this strips InvariantTypes of their invariance!
        Returns:
        The primitive value

      • getUpdatable

        public Value getUpdatable(ValueListenerList listeners)
        Return an UpdatableValue, wrapping this one. This is a deep translation that recurses into all Values that contain other Values (sets etc), converting their contents to UpdateableValues. The results can then be modified in assignment statements or used as state data etc.
        Parameters:
        listeners - The listener to inform of updates to the value.
        Returns:
        An UpdatableValue for this one.

      • getConstant

        public Value getConstant()
        Return a simple Value, removing any Updatable/TransactionValue wrappers. This is the opposite of getUpdatable(), though it works for all values. Note that this will preserve InvariantValues' integrity (unlike deref).
        Returns:
        A simple value
